My fandom name is Beachy, and this is a multi-fandom blog. 
I'm also a multi-shipper. It's likely I do not sail your ship, but I don't wank and expect visitors to play nicely as well. That includes not adding hate or negativity to my posts, altering them to suit your own ships, or removing my original comments. If you do, you will be blocked.
IRL they call me Doctor. Yep, I'm that old. Sometimes I write things that other people watch. It's all good! I like mocha latte with bourbon. A lot.

summary:
BAD SAMARITAN: "He's Damaged Goods" - David Tennant Talks To Starburst About His Chilling Character  

Ahead of the UK release...
caption:
BAD SAMARITAN: “He’s Damaged Goods” - David Tennant Talks To Starburst About His Chilling Character 

Ahead of the UK release of Bad Samaritan later this month, the film’s star David Tennant and its creators Dean Devlin and Brandon Boyce have been talking to Starburst Magazine about the nailbiting thriller. Written by Boyce and produced and directed by Devlin, the film stars Robert Sheehan and Carlito Olivero as a pair of parking valets and petty criminals who stumble upon a terrifying secret during a break in. David turns in a chilling performance as Cale Erendreich, the psychopathic homeowner, who makes it his mission to destroy the lives of the hapless burglars.

summary: Imagine: Saving The Doctor from an alien threat.
body:
Imagine: Saving The Doctor from an alien threat.

“DOCTOR!” You screamed. Nothing. You felt a lump in your throat, he had promised to you he would come back and you were starting to get the feeling he was in danger. You ran out of the tardis and onto the unknown planet. “DOCTOR, DOCTOR WHERE ARE YOU!” You yelled again.


Still nothing.


You heard hissing in the distance. You ran to the noise. An alien creature was cornering The Doctor. You quietly and quickly snuck behind it and, gripped the hammer in your hand. “Argh!” You groaned swinging the hammer and, hitting the creature in the back of the head. You sigh.


“Doctor, are you alright?” You asked, lowering the weapon.


The Doctor nodded. “Alright thanks to you.”


Requested by: Anonymous
